name: ○ Schletter FS DUO - Fixed-tilt Installation Procedure
○ Piles distributed as per Schletter drawings, ie correct colour, code , dimensions and length
Drive piles to depth until they reach the point of refusal
Record Pile location and mark on the drawing
Pile refusal in accordance with pile refusal procedure
Piles cut and holes drilled as per Schletter documentation
ITC Data Tracker Excel Pile Monitoring Sheet
Predrill holes are minimum of 300mm dia
Backfilled with approved mix as per Schletters Installation Procedure
Schletter FS Duo Fixed-tilt Installation Procedure
Install Pile on the correct location as per Schletter drawing
Install pile within the design tolerances
Piles should have no damage or deformation and in correct orientation
Height difference foundation posts within one row +/- 50mm
Piles have no damage deformation and in correct orientation
Schletter FS Duo Fixed-tilt Installation Procedure
Upper 30mm of the inside and outside of the pile is coated with a zinc rich primer
Schletter FS Duo - Fixed Tilt Instalation Procedure - Item 9.0
Each M12x30 bolt passed through from the Girder and fixed on the Pile with a M12 Washer and M12 Flange Serrated Nut
Torqued to value of +/- 5% of 53.2 - 58.8 Nm
Each bolted connection shall be marked after torquing
Girder to Foundation Post Step Check
Schletter FS Duo - Fixed Tilt Instalation Procedure - Item 9.0
Angle of the Girder to the horizontal to be an angle of 23° +/- 1°
Schletter FS Duo - Fixed Tilt Instalation Procedure - Item 10
Screwed together with Four x M10x25 bolts for LC/LT Purlins
Tightened to a torqued value of +/- 5% of 32Nm
Each bolted connection shall be marked after torquing
Schletter FS Duo - Fixed Tilt Instalation Procedure - Item 10
Purlin placed on top of the girder in correct direction
FS Gen3 Girder Purlin connector bottom part attached
Schletter FS Duo - Fixed Tilt Instalation Procedure - Item 10
M10x35 bolt and nut tightened to a torque of +/- 5% of 32Nm
M21x30 bolt and nut tightened to a torque of +/- 5% of 56Nm
Each Non-Conformance Reported, Rectified & Closed Out
Works completed for the table and checked
Schletter FS DUO - Fixed-tilt Installation Procedure
Schletter FS DUO - Fixed-tilt Installation Procedure
Align Module and gap between panels as per IFC Drawings
Schletter FS DUO - Fixed-tilt Installation Procedure
Ensure Panels are dry, clean of dust/mud and no visible damage
Schletter FS DUO - Fixed-tilt Installation Procedure
Ensure Panels Start and Finish at even distances of the Purlin
Panels shall be 50mm from the ends of the purlins
Ensure correct number of panels are installed for each table
Schletter FS DUO - Fixed-tilt Installation Procedure
Each Non-Conformance Reported, Rectified & Closed Out
Works completed for the table and checked
